    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE production_line (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    line_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE production (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);

    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);

    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);


CREATE TABLE product (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    manufacturer_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (manufacturer_id) REFERENCES manufacturer(id)
);
</t><stat>insert into product (id, name, price, manufacturer_id) select 7, 'product7', 40.99, 1 from manufacturer where id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE manufacturer (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    line_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE production (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);

    line_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE production (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_line_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    production_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES product(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (production_line_id) REFERENCES production_line(id)
);


CREATE TABLE manufacturer (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE product (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    manufacturer_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (manufacturer_id) REFERENCES manufacturer(id)
);
